Overall, we observed significant differences in protein levels between mucinous and non-mucinous fractions of lipid (fatty acid) metabolism proteins such as Glutathione S-transferase (Table 2B); energy associated proteins such as those involved in glucose metabolism and ATP synthesis e.g. Pyruvate kinase isozymes M1/M2 (Table 2A and ​and2B)2B) as well as stress related proteins such as heat shock cognate 71kDa, heat shock 70kDa protein 1-like, and heat shock 70kDa protein 6 (Table 2B).

