Hemodynamics indices in NaCl- and NaHCO3-treated Dahl SS rats fed a high salt diet
NaHCO3 had no significant effect on daily mean arterial pressure (Figure 2) or proteinuria (Figure 2) in Dahl SS rats when compared with vehicle. NaHCO3 increased renal arterial blood velocity when animals were fed LS; however, renal arterial blood velocity increased to similar levels in both vehicle- and NaHCO3-treated animals following initiation of an HS diet (Figure 2).

